Load datasets¶

In [3]:
# Load tips data from seaborn libraries
tips = sns.load_dataset("tips")
print(tips.head())

# Load penguins dataset and remove na values
penguins = load_penguins()
penguins = penguins.dropna()
print(penguins.head())

1.1 Facet Grid Plot¶

In [4]:
tips.day.unique()
Out[4]:
['Sun', 'Sat', 'Thur', 'Fri']
Categories (4, object): ['Sun', 'Sat', 'Thur', 'Fri']
In [5]:
g1 = sns.FacetGrid(data = tips,
                    col = "day",
                    row_order=["Sat", "Sun", "Thur", "Fri"])

g1.map(sns.scatterplot,
       "total_bill",
       "tip")

plt.show()

1.2 Relational plot¶

In [26]:
sns.relplot(x = "total_bill",
            y = "tip",
            data = tips,
            kind = "scatter",
            col = "day")
plt.show()

1.3 Factor Plot¶

In [28]:
sns.catplot(x = "sex",
            y = "tip",
            data = tips,
            kind = "violin",
            col = "day")

plt.show()

1.4 lmplot()¶

In [36]:
col_order = ['Lunch','Dinner']

sns.lmplot(x = 'total_bill',
           y = 'tip',
           data = tips,
           col = "time",
           row = 'sex',
           row_order = ["Male", "Female"],
           hue = 'day',
           col_order = col_order)

plt.show()
plt.clf()

2. PairGrid and PairPlot¶

2.1 Pair Grid¶

In [9]:
penguins.columns
Out[9]:
Index(['species', 'island', 'bill_length_mm', 'bill_depth_mm',
       'flipper_length_mm', 'body_mass_g', 'sex', 'year'],
      dtype='object')
In [10]:
g = sns.PairGrid(penguins, 
                  vars=['bill_length_mm', 'bill_depth_mm',
                       'flipper_length_mm', 'body_mass_g'])
g2 = g.map_diag(plt.hist)
g3 = g2.map_offdiag(plt.scatter)

plt.show()
plt.clf()

<Figure size 432x288 with 0 Axes>

2.2 Pair Plots¶

In [11]:
sns.pairplot(vars = ['bill_length_mm', 'bill_depth_mm',
                       'flipper_length_mm', 'body_mass_g'],
             data = penguins,
             kind = 'scatter',
             diag_kind = "hist",
             hue = 'species',
             palette = "Set1",
             diag_kws = {'alpha':.5})

plt.show()
plt.clf()

<Figure size 432x288 with 0 Axes>
In [12]:
sns.pairplot(vars = ['bill_length_mm', 'bill_depth_mm',
                       'flipper_length_mm', 'body_mass_g'],
             data = penguins,
             kind = 'reg',
             diag_kind = "kde",
             hue = 'species',
             palette = "Set1",
             diag_kws = {'alpha': 0.4})

plt.show()
plt.clf()

3. JointGrid() and jointplot()¶

3.1 JointGrid()¶

In [13]:
sns.set_style("whitegrid")

g = sns.JointGrid(x="total_bill",
                  y="tip",
                  data = tips) 

g.plot(sns.regplot, sns.histplot)

plt.show()
plt.clf()
